Lagos â€“ Governor Seyi Makinde has been declared the winner of March 9th governorship election in Oyo State by Supreme Court. In a court judgement in the Oyo State Governorship election appeal between Seyi Makinde and Adebayo Adelabu, candidate of All Progressives Congress (APC), delivered by Justice Ukaego Mary Peter-Odili, who presided over the Oyo State Election Appeal at the Supreme Court in Abuja. The Court allowed appeal, while the majority judgement of the Court of Appeal were set aside which implied that Makinde remained the governor. The judgment had put a final rest to the power tussle between the PDP and APC in Oyo State.